  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study purpose is to examine polymorphism of genes associated to post-operative persistent
      pain and to verify the possible association between genotype phenotype and ADRB2 polymorphism
      in orthopaedic surgery. The primary aim is to evaluate the expression of ADBR2 in VAS&gt;4
      patients and to compare it to those with VAS&lt;4.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
